FBIS4-19842 "drweu079_e_94005" FBIS-WEU-94-079 Daily Report 23 Apr 1994 UNITED KINGDOM Major Pays Tribute to Nixon Major Pays Tribute to Nixon LD2304174894 London PRESS ASSOCIATION in English 1722 GMT 23 Apr 94 LD2304174894 London PRESS ASSOCIATION English BFN [Text] The Prime Minister today paid tribute to the role that the Richard Nixon played in ending the Cold War between East and West. In a message to President Bill Clinton, John Major said he had heard "with sadness" the news of the former president's death. "I send to you and to the American people my sympathy and condolences," he said. "Richard Nixon will be remembered for his tireless work for a better understanding between East and West. He was a leading architect of the process which led to the end of the Cold War and his judgment on international affairs was widely respected. He will be greatly missed by his many friends and admirers on this side of the Atlantic." Contents of the message were released by the Foreign Office.
